Title : Portland Thunderbirds
Text : The '''Portland Thunderbirds''', formerly the '''Portland Pioneers''', were a [[semi-professional]] [[American football]] team based in [[Portland, Oregon]] from 1961–66. They played at [[Multnomah Stadium]] (now known as Providence Park).

==History==
An amateur football team known as the "Pioneers" played in 1961, but not in an organized league.<ref>{{cite news|last=Fair|first=Don|title=Am football league set|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=17 July 1962|page=23}}</ref> In 1962 the North Pacific Amateur Football League was formed, which barred players with professional football experience. The Portland team renamed themselves the "Thunderbirds".<ref>{{cite news|last=Fair|first=Don|title=Portland grid entry seeks depth in line|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=23 August 1962|page=51}}</ref> The team returned in 1963 with John Moynihan as [[head coach]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Amateurs set football loop|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=14 April 1963|agency=Associated Press}}</ref> The league was renamed the North Pacific Football League and reclassified as a [[semi-professional]] circuit.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tyees drop T-birds, 13–7|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=23 September 1963}}</ref> That year the Thunderbirds held practices at [[Delta Park]] in [[North Portland, Oregon|North Portland]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Thunderbirds summon squad|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=28 June 1963|page=95}}</ref> The Thunderbirds joined the newly formed Pacific Coast Semi-Pro Football League in 1964.<ref>{{cite news|title='Birds open on Sunday|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=5 September 1964|page=19}}</ref> They were sponsored by the Portland Junior Chamber of Commerce that year.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gregory|first=L. H.|title=T-birds gain JC support|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=19 August 1964|page=36}}</ref> Plans to join the [[Continental Football League]] failed in 1967, and the Thunderbirds subsequently disbanded.<ref>{{cite news|title=Group plans T-birds entry|newspaper=The Oregonian |page=64 |date= 14 August 1967}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gregory|first=L. H.|title=Greg's gossip|newspaper=The Oregonian|page=52}}</ref>

